Share Context: Jira Context
Param: site_id: The ID of the Jira site to get the issue in
Param: issue_key: The key of the issue to get

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getIssue

---
Name: Get Issue Types
Description: Gets the issue types in a Jira project. Each Jira project can have different issue types, so this is useful to get the issue types for a specific project, and can then be used to create an issue.
Share Tools: Get Project, Get All Projects
Credential: ../credential
Share Context: Jira Context
Param: site_id: The ID of the Jira site to get the issue types in
Param: project_id_or_key: The ID or key of the project to get the issue types in

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getIssueTypes

---
Name: Get Priority Schemes
Description: Gets the priority schemes in a Jira instance.
Credential: ../credential
Share Context: Jira Context
Param: site_id: The ID of the Jira site to get the priority schemes in

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getPrioritySchemes

---
Name: Get Available Priorities
Description: Gets the available priorities of a priority scheme. if no scheme_id is provided, it will get the default priority scheme.
Share Tools: Get Priority Schemes
Credential: ../credential
Share Context: Jira Context
Param: site_id: The ID of the Jira site to get the available priorities in
Param: scheme_id: Optional, the ID of the priority scheme to get the available priorities in.

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getAvailablePriorities

---
Name: Create Issue
Description: Creates an issue in a Jira project
Share Tools: Get Issue Types, Get Available Priorities, Get User, Get Project
Credential: ../credential
Share Context: Jira Context
Param: site_id: The ID of the Jira site to create the issue in
Param: project_id: The ID of the project to create the issue in
Param: summary: The summary/title of the issue
Param: description: Optional, the description of the issue.
Param: issue_type: Optional, the type of the issue
Param: priority: Optional, the priority of the issue
Param: assignee_id: Optional, the account ID of the assignee of the issue
Param: reporter_id: Optional, the account ID of the reporter of the issue

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js createIssue

---
Name: Jira Context
Type: context
Share Tools: List Jira Sites, Get Current User

#!/sys.echo

## START INSTRUCTIONS: Jira Tools

You have access to tools for interacting with Jira.
If you don't know what Jira Sites are available for the current user, call the List Jira Sites tool
to get the list of sites that the user has access to.
Tools that require a site_id must be called with a site_id from the Jira Sites that are available for the current user.
If you don't have info about current user's Jira account, call the Get Current User tool.

## END INSTRUCTIONS: Jira Tools

